            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Actually if message was parsed I also want to know where it ended, so I can cut a string properly and make another call. Sorry, actually I wanted that thing (forgot about second return value, sorry for misleading):\n\n```lua\n---@param data string\n---@param offset? integer -- Message's first byte position (1 by default)\n---@return any? -- The parsed message (or nil if message was partial)\n---@return integer? -- Next message's first byte position in data\nfunction vim.mpack.decode_one(data, offset) end\n```\n\n```lua\nrecd_data = recd_data .. chunk_received_from_pipe\nwhile recd_data ~= \"\" do\n  local msg, new_pos = vim.mpack.decode_one(recd_data, 1)\n  if not msg then\n    -- Partial message\n    break\n  end\n  recd_data = recd_data:sub(new_pos)\n  handle_msg(msg)\nend\n```",
