            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "```lua\n--- I don't know how to name this flag)\n---@param str string\n---@param flag? boolean -- If true then return [object, new_position]\n---@return any\n---@return integer?\nfunction vim.mpack.decode(str, flag) end\n```\n\nIf something like that, then it's also perfectly fine for my use case\n\nP.S. In [this](https://github.com/kieselsteini/msgpack#msgpackdecode_onebinary_data-position) library similar function returns `[object_or_nil, new_position_or_error_string]`. But maybe it's better to return `[object, new_position]` or throw the error (to not break old **vim.mpack.decode** logic). Then it would be something like that?:\n\n```lua\nrecd_data = recd_data .. chunk_received_from_pipe\nwhile recd_data ~= \"\" do\n  local ok, msg, new_pos = pcall(vim.mpack.decode_one, recd_data, true)\n  if not ok then\n    -- Error, try with more data later\n    ---@cast msg string\n    vim.print(msg)\n    break\n  end\n  recd_data = recd_data:sub(new_pos)\n  handle_msg(msg)\nend\n```",
